$ /etc/dpkg/dpkg.cfg

`/etc/dpkg/dpkg.cfg` is the configuration file for `→ Linux/distributions/Debian/dpkg` and stores
default (command line?) options for `dpkg`.


code {
# Do not enable debsig-verify by default; since the distribution is not using
# embedded signatures, debsig-verify would reject all packages.
no-debsig

# Log status changes and actions to a file.
log → Linux/fhs/var/log/dpkg_log
code }
